We knows, maximum velocity $V_{\max }=A \omega=A \sqrt{\frac{K}{m}}$
Given,
$$
\begin{gathered}
K_1, m_1=m, K_2, m_2=2 m \\
\left(V_{\max }\right)_A=\left(V_{\max }\right)_B
\end{gathered}
$$
$$
\begin{aligned}
\quad A_A \sqrt{\frac{K_1}{M}} &amp; =A_B \sqrt{\frac{K_2}{2 m}} \\
\Rightarrow \quad \frac{A_A}{A_B} &amp; =\sqrt{\frac{K_2}{2 K_1}}
\end{aligned}
$$
